          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>The <fr:em>judgements</fr:em> over a <fr:link type="local" href="signature.xml" addr="signature" title="Signature">signature</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> are defined as follows.
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[     \mathcal {J} :=       \mathcal {R}(\overline {e}) \,\, | \,\,       \{x\} \, \mathcal {J} \,\, | \,\,       \mathcal {J} \vdash  \mathcal {J}   ]]></fr:tex>
  The proof rules for judgements are (and this is intentional) extremely simple.
  <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {R}(\overline {e})]]></fr:tex>: Supplied by the background <fr:link type="local" href="theory.xml" addr="theory" title="Theories">theory</fr:link></fr:li>
    <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{x\} \, \mathcal {J}]]></fr:tex>: Abstraction and specialization</fr:li>
    <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {H} \vdash  \mathcal {J}]]></fr:tex>: Abstraction and application</fr:li></fr:ul></fr:p>
